Introduction
The Inventory Management System is a powerful tool for managing product inventories, tracking transactions, and automating reorders. Designed for efficiency and scalability, the system supports multiple users with varying levels of permissions.

Main Features
Product Management:

Add, delete, and edit products in the inventory.
Transaction Tracking:

Monitor transactions by product.
View changes made and who made them.
Automated Reordering:

Option to automate reorders from suppliers.
Reporting:

Export stock change reports to your computer.
User Permissions:

Admins have enhanced permissions compared to regular users.
Getting Started
Clone the Repository
To begin, clone the repository using the following command:

bash
Kopioi koodi
git clone https://github.com/Jafestro/Inventory-Management-Sys.git
Database Setup
Create a database:
sql
Kopioi koodi
CREATE DATABASE {yourdatabasename};
USE {yourdatabasename};
Apply the provided SQL script to add necessary tables and columns.
Set Up Database Connection
Locate the application.properties file in the project.
Fill in your database credentials:
Database name
Username
Password
Run the Application
To start the application, execute the following commands:

Build the project:

bash
Kopioi koodi
mvn clean install
Run the application:

bash
Kopioi koodi
mvn clean javafx:run
Technologies Used
Java: Core programming language.
Spring Boot: Framework for backend development.
Maven: Build automation tool.
JavaFX: For building the graphical user interface.
MariaDB: Database for storing inventory data.
JUnit: Framework for testing.
Jacoco: Code coverage tool.
Jenkins: Continuous integration and delivery platform.
